Lite Plate is a very simple CMS and it should not be considered totally secure.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To Install:
1.) copy all files into your web directory
2.) either:
-import the install_lite_plate.sql file using phpmyadmin
-or using the terminal: $ mysql -u root -p lite_plate < lite_plate.sql
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Functions:

Constructor:
  -parameters:
    -$title (string) - the title which displays in the browser window
    -$body_id (string) - id for the <body> element; used to distinguish active pages
  -logic:
-sets title to '$title'
-sets body_id to '$body_id'
-calls $database's constructor; creates a database object for the page
--------------------
display Function:
  -logic:
-connects to mysql
-starts gzip compress
-sends expires header
-sends content header
-outputs page using template.php
-disconnects from mysql
  -parameters:
-$page (string) - name of the page you want to get content for
-queries 'node1_content' table for a row where the 'page' column equals '$page'
-returns array '$content' containing left column, right column, and footer content
--------------------
get_bodyid Function:
  -logic:
-gets value of url parameter '$_GET['node1']'
-sanitizes '$_GET['node1']'
-if the '$_GET['node1']' parameter is used the id of <body> is set to the value of '$_GET['node1']'
-else the id of <body> is set to 'home'
--------------------
get_navigation Function:
  -logic:
-gets value of url parameter '$_GET['node1']'
-sanitizes '$_GET['node1']'
-queries mysql database for the name, path, and titles of all the navigation links
-for each row in the query result output the link, and its title
-if the current row contains the page on which the user's browser is pointed, that link will be highlited as active
